Adapter behavior (per F.3 spec `do` clause):
  ✓ Adapter object: toolkit='googlesheets', events=[
    'GOOGLESHEETS_NEW_ROWS_TRIGGER'] — registers under both fields so
    F.2's getAdapter(toolkit, event) lookup returns the adapter only
    when BOTH match.
  ✓ initialState: calls Composio /tools/execute/GOOGLESHEETS_BATCH_GET
    with arguments={ spreadsheet_id, ranges: ['<sheet>!A1:Z'] }; parses
    valueRanges[0].values; counts non-empty rows (countNonEmptyRows
    uses last-non-empty-index+1, so trailing empty padding from Sheets
    API is correctly discarded); returns
    { last_row_count: N, header_row?: <row 0> } — header_row included
    only when start_row > 1 OR cfg.header_row !== false.
  ✓ poll: same call; compares currentCount vs prev state.last_row_count.
      - currentCount === prev: emits zero events, preserves state.
      - currentCount > prev: emits one PollAdapterEvent per row in the
        index range [prev, currentCount). Payload shape exactly
        matches Composio's native GOOGLESHEETS_NEW_ROWS_TRIGGER:
          { row_number (1-based absolute), row_data, sheet_name,
            spreadsheet_id, detected_at } plus an extra header_row hint
        that the cron-kicker's buildInputs uses to produce keyed
        `row` objects (mirror of D.5's pickInputMapper).
      - currentCount < prev (sheet shrank): emits zero events, logs
        console.warn, resyncs nextState.last_row_count to current
        instead of preserving the higher prior value. NEVER emits
        synthetic "row deleted" events (Composio's webhook trigger
        never delivers these either, so consistency holds).
  ✓ Failure modes throw cleanly so the cron-kicker's circuit-breaker
    (consecutive_failures + paused_at at >=5) counts them:
      - HTTP non-2xx → throw `${TOOL_SLUG} HTTP <code>` with body
      - successful=false envelope on 200 → throw with error message
      - Missing spreadsheet_id in config → throw on first call

